! CSBB Dispatch: Cross-Domain Content Delivery — Built 5 Years Before Content Controller
''Summary:'' Centralized cross-domain content delivery: lightweight stub packages (kilobytes) deployed to client LMS platforms, actual content served from GP servers. EasyXDM cross-domain communication layer with transparent SCORM/AICC protocol translation. Package generation tooling (Groovy, Access, Windows Forms) automated global deployments across ~20 energy utility clients. ~2,000 course library (curated subsets per client), 10+ years in production. Architecture later adapted for General Dynamics Electric Boat defense sector.
''Role:'' Architect — built in 2011, five years before Rustici Content Controller
''Date:'' 2011–2016+
''Email count:'' 10+ years in production

! Context

Architected a cross-domain content delivery system serving ~20 energy utility clients through a centralized SCORM dispatch layer — each drawing a curated subset from a ~2,000 course central library. Eliminated the manual zip-and-email deployment cycle. Built in 2011 — five years before Rustici released Content Controller to solve the same problem.

